translated: Domeij, Nilis Göte, former provincial medical officer, born on 12/6/06 in Fredrika, Västerbotten County. His parents are Albert D. and Margareta Wiklund. He graduated from high school in Umeå in 1927, received his medical degree in Stockholm in 1931, and obtained a medical license there in 1935. He served as an assistant doctor at the military hospital in Eksjö in 1933, as a temporary and regular assistant doctor in the surgical department of St. Göran's Hospital in 1936, as a temporary and acting assistant doctor at Styrsö Coastal Sanatorium from 1936-1937, as an assistant doctor and temporary second assistant doctor in the medical department of Gävle Hospital from 1937-1938, as an assistant doctor and doctor in the surgical department there in 1938, as a temporary second assistant doctor at Visby Hospital from 1938-1939, and as the first medical officer there from 1940-1942 (in the meantime, he was temporary medical officer for three months). He was also the first assistant doctor in the surgical department of Skellefteå Hospital from 1942-1944 (in the meantime, he was temporary medical officer for three months) and the second assistant doctor at Hällnäs Sanatorium from 1944-1945. He served as the acting assistant doctor at the Epidemic Hospital in Gothenburg in 1945 and became a provincial medical officer in Vedum's district in 1946.
